    "html": "<h1 id=\"-subway-builder-savefile-doctor\">üè• Subway Builder Savefile Doctor</h1>\n<p>A beautiful TUI (Text User Interface) tool for editing Subway Builder save files.</p>\n<h2 id=\"desktop-app\">Desktop App</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/ejfox/metro-savefile-doctor/releases/latest\">Download the latest release</a></strong></p>\n<p>Cross-platform desktop app with a crackintro aesthetic:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>macOS</strong>: <code>.dmg</code> (Apple Silicon &amp; Intel)</li>\n<li><strong>Windows</strong>: <code>.msi</code> installer</li>\n<li><strong>Linux</strong>: <code>.AppImage</code> / <code>.deb</code> / <code>.rpm</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Features drag &amp; drop, quick editing, analysis reports, and auto-backup.</p>\n<h2 id=\"features\">Features</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>üí∞ <strong>Edit Money</strong> - Give yourself unlimited cash</li>\n<li>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>Edit Game Time</strong> - Change elapsed simulation time</li>\n<li>üöÜ <strong>Edit Train Count</strong> - Change owned train count</li>\n<li>üé´ <strong>Edit Transit Cost</strong> - Change ticket price for riders</li>\n<li>üíæ <strong>Auto Backup</strong> - Creates backups before modifying</li>\n<li>üì¶ <strong>Binary Format Support</strong> - Handles both JSON and .metro binary saves</li>\n<li>‚ú® <strong>Beautiful TUI</strong> - Interactive terminal interface with colors</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"installation\">Installation</h2>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">cd tools/savefile-doctor\nnpm install\nchmod +x cli.js\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"usage\">Usage</h2>\n<h3 id=\"basic-usage\">Basic Usage</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\"># Edit a .metro binary save file (creates backup automatically)\n./cli.js ~/Documents/SubwayBuilder/my-save.metro\n\n# Or edit a JSON save file\n./cli.js ~/path/to/your-save.json\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"advanced-options\">Advanced Options</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\"># Save to a different file\n./cli.js my-save.json --output modified-save.json\n\n# Don't create backup\n./cli.js my-save.json --no-backup\n\n# Install globally\nnpm link\nsavefile-doctor ~/saves/my-save.json\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"controls\">Controls</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Arrow Keys</strong> - Navigate menu</li>\n<li><strong>Enter</strong> - Edit selected field</li>\n<li><strong>Escape</strong> - Cancel editing</li>\n<li><strong>s</strong> - Save changes</li>\n<li><strong>q</strong> - Quit (without saving if you haven't pressed 's')</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"examples\">Examples</h2>\n<h3 id=\"give-yourself-money\">Give Yourself Money</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the tool: <code>./cli.js my-save.metro</code></li>\n<li>Select \"üí∞ Money\"</li>\n<li>Enter new amount (e.g., <code>999999999</code>)</li>\n<li>Press Enter</li>\n<li>Press 's' to save</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"fix-train-count\">Fix Train Count</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the tool: <code>./cli.js my-save.metro</code></li>\n<li>Select \"üöÜ Owned Trains\"</li>\n<li>Enter new count (e.g., <code>100</code>)</li>\n<li>Press Enter</li>\n<li>Press 's' to save</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"safety\">Safety</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Automatic Backups</strong>: By default, creates <code>.backup</code> file before modifying</li>\n<li><strong>Validation</strong>: Checks file format before editing</li>\n<li><strong>Non-Destructive</strong>: Original file preserved unless you save changes</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"requirements\">Requirements</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Node.js 18+</li>\n<li>Subway Builder save file (.metro binary or JSON format)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"supported-formats\">Supported Formats</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>üì¶ .metro files</strong> - Binary format with 4KB header, compressed game data, and metadata</li>\n<li><strong>üìÑ JSON files</strong> - Plain JSON save files</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The tool automatically detects the format and handles both seamlessly.</p>\n<h2 id=\"troubleshooting\">Troubleshooting</h2>\n<p><strong>\"Invalid save file format\"</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Make sure you're using a Subway Builder save file</li>\n<li>File must be valid JSON with <code>data</code> and <code>version</code> fields</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>\"File not found\"</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Check the file path is correct</li>\n<li>Use absolute paths or relative to current directory</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"technical-details\">Technical Details</h2>\n<p>Built with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink\">Ink</a> - React for CLIs</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/chalk/chalk\">Chalk</a> - Terminal colors</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/meow\">Meow</a> - CLI argument parsing</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"license\">License</h2>\n<p>MIT</p>",
    "raw": "# üè• Subway Builder Savefile Doctor\n\nA beautiful TUI (Text User Interface) tool for editing Subway Builder save files.\n\n## Desktop App\n\n**[Download the latest release](https://github.com/ejfox/metro-savefile-doctor/releases/latest)**\n\nCross-platform desktop app with a crackintro aesthetic:\n- **macOS**: `.dmg` (Apple Silicon & Intel)\n- **Windows**: `.msi` installer\n- **Linux**: `.AppImage` / `.deb` / `.rpm`\n\nFeatures drag & drop, quick editing, analysis reports, and auto-backup.\n\n## Features\n\n- üí∞ **Edit Money** - Give yourself unlimited cash\n- ‚è±Ô∏è **Edit Game Time** - Change elapsed simulation time\n- üöÜ **Edit Train Count** - Change owned train count\n- üé´ **Edit Transit Cost** - Change ticket price for riders\n- üíæ **Auto Backup** - Creates backups before modifying\n- üì¶ **Binary Format Support** - Handles both JSON and .metro binary saves\n- ‚ú® **Beautiful TUI** - Interactive terminal interface with colors\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\ncd tools/savefile-doctor\nnpm install\nchmod +x cli.js\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Basic Usage\n\n```bash\n# Edit a .metro binary save file (creates backup automatically)\n./cli.js ~/Documents/SubwayBuilder/my-save.metro\n\n# Or edit a JSON save file\n./cli.js ~/path/to/your-save.json\n```\n\n### Advanced Options\n\n```bash\n# Save to a different file\n./cli.js my-save.json --output modified-save.json\n\n# Don't create backup\n./cli.js my-save.json --no-backup\n\n# Install globally\nnpm link\nsavefile-doctor ~/saves/my-save.json\n```\n\n## Controls\n\n- **Arrow Keys** - Navigate menu\n- **Enter** - Edit selected field\n- **Escape** - Cancel editing\n- **s** - Save changes\n- **q** - Quit (without saving if you haven't pressed 's')\n\n## Examples\n\n### Give Yourself Money\n\n1. Run the tool: `./cli.js my-save.metro`\n2. Select \"üí∞ Money\"\n3. Enter new amount (e.g., `999999999`)\n4. Press Enter\n5. Press 's' to save\n\n### Fix Train Count\n\n1. Run the tool: `./cli.js my-save.metro`\n2. Select \"üöÜ Owned Trains\"\n3. Enter new count (e.g., `100`)\n4. Press Enter\n5. Press 's' to save\n\n## Safety\n\n- **Automatic Backups**: By default, creates `.backup` file before modifying\n- **Validation**: Checks file format before editing\n- **Non-Destructive**: Original file preserved unless you save changes\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Node.js 18+\n- Subway Builder save file (.metro binary or JSON format)\n\n## Supported Formats\n\n- **üì¶ .metro files** - Binary format with 4KB header, compressed game data, and metadata\n- **üìÑ JSON files** - Plain JSON save files\n\nThe tool automatically detects the format and handles both seamlessly.\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n**\"Invalid save file format\"**\n\n- Make sure you're using a Subway Builder save file\n- File must be valid JSON with `data` and `version` fields\n\n**\"File not found\"**\n\n- Check the file path is correct\n- Use absolute paths or relative to current directory\n\n## Technical Details\n\nBuilt with:\n\n- [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink) - React for CLIs\n- [Chalk](https://github.com/chalk/chalk) - Terminal colors\n- [Meow](https://github.com/sindresorhus/meow) - CLI argument parsing\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n",
